öglich. Deswegen sollte vom Einsatz dieses Rationierungskriteriums abgesehen werden.   aThis work explores a controversial strategy for dealing with the chronic financial deficits in our health care system – namely, rationing based on the criterion of personal responsibility. It argues that while rationing by personal responsibility is basically morally permissible, it is only possible in a very limited number of instances. For this reason, the use of this rationing criterion should be rejected.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 4aGesundheitssystem. 4aHealth Care Ethics. 4aPersonhood. 4aRationing. 4aResponsibility. 4aVerantwortung. 4aWirtschaftsethik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2015z9783110438680oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97815015018830 cprintz978150151054040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150150183840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501501838423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501501838.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DPHb2015